What you need to know:

The Reds trail surprise leaders Manchester United by six points, but play their game in hand when Burnley visit Anfield on ThursdayConcern over Liverpool's ability to retain the title has grown in recent weeks after a run of three league games without a goal for the first time since 2005With over half the season to play, Klopp is expecting plenty more twists and turns before a decisive move is made in the title race